| award1Pub = [[Spike Video Game Awards]]
| award1 = Best Game Based on a Movie or TV Show (2009)<ref name="spikeawards_d6">{{Cite web |url=http://www.doublesixgames.com/south-park-lets-go-tower-defense-play-wins-award/ |title=South Park Let<U+2019>s Go Tower Defense Play Wins Award |author=User "Ollie" |date=December 18, 2009 |publisher=[[Doublesix]] |accessdate=September 4, 2011}}</ref>
}}

The game was first mentioned at the 2008 [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]] (E3),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.southparkstudios.com/news/357361/south-park-on-xbox-live|title=South Park on Xbox Live |accessdate=September 4, 2011|date=July 16, 2008|publisher=South Park Studios}}</ref> and was later revealed with its final title at [[San Diego Comic-Con International|Comic-Con]] 2009.<ref name="comiccon_panel" /> It was released on October 7, 2009, the day the second half of the show's [[South Park (season 13)|thirteenth season]] premiered.<ref name="gametrailers_interview" /> In October 2009, as part of Xbox Live's "Game with Fame" promotion, players were able to play with series co-creator [[Matt Stone]], and other South Park Studios employees online.<ref name="gamewithfame">{{Cite web |url=http://www.southparkstudios.com/games/lgtdp/game-with-fame |title=''Let's Go Tower Defense Play!'': Game with Fame |date=October 19, 2009 |publisher=South Park Studios |accessdate=September 4, 2011}}</ref>

[[GameSpot]] gave the game a 7.5 out of 10 saying "A great sense of humor and challenging gameplay make Let's Go Tower Defense Play! easily the best South Park game to date."<ref name="review_gspot" /> [[IGN]] gave the game a 7.0 out of 10 because of the story, non-stop nostalgia, and having the game have more of a multiplayer focus, making the game frustrating for solo gamers.<ref name="ign_review" /> At the 2009 [[Spike Video Game Awards]], the game was awarded the "Best Game Based on a Movie or TV Show" award.<ref name="spikeawards_d6" />

